description: Meet the newest and most dangerous member of the Tweedle gang—Tweedle Die! But is Batman ready to take on this muscular madman in the skies of Gotham City? Plus, the new Batmobile makes its debut!
name: Roadkill Part 2 of 2

description:
Introduced by your host, The Bloke, a Victorian undertaker, who I dress as at conventions to promote the magazine. Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror is a homage to the classic horror anthology magazines that we grew up loving.

This is an ongoing, self-published series, with eleven issues currently available and two collected editions. Voted Best Anthology Of 2013 in the Ghastly Awards.

Writers - Jason 'The Bloke' Crawley & Mike Hoffman Artwork - Mike Hoffman, Juan Carlos Abraldes Rendo, Nik Poliwko, Jeff Austin, Rock Baker, Scott Shriver, Maurizio Ercole, Todd Kennedy & Samuel Agro.

Rob's second issue of his awesome four issue CW mini-series finds Professor Cook and Lt. Mack arriving back in town and finding out that Meriem has already returned. Panic spreads through Marshville due to the Blackstone Gang's attacks and Meriem will not leave Bruce's side in the hospital. Nathan and his family arrives on the outskirts of town, just in time to see it burn. Can it get any worse?

Expanded to more than twice the length of the previous volumes, Dungeon Quest Book Three continues the adventures of Millennium Boy, Steve, Lash and Nerdgirl as they traverse mysterious underground realms. This latest installment of the stoner D&D epic brings a whole new level of bizarre comedy, rousing adventure and ass-kicking action - all staged in front of fantastic backdrops replete with strange vegetation, ancient ruins and steam-punk imagery.

76 pages of Mutant Mayhem!

X-Men past, present and future fight to survive against the power of SHIELD – and all the teams will never be the same again! Don't miss the conclusion of 'Battle of the Atom'! By Jason Aaron, Esad Ribic and Giuseppe Camuncoli!

Featuring material first published in X-Men: Battle of the Atom #2, All-New X-Men #18 and Uncanny X-Men #14.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 413: The Tome of E.N.D. (ＥＮＤの書)
  • Chapter 414: Drops of Fire (炎の雫)
  • Chapter 415: That Is the Power of Life (それが生きる力だ)
  • Chapter 416: Tartaros Arc, Final Part (冥府の門編 【終章】)
  • Chapter 417: Lone Journey II (一人旅Ⅱ)
  • Chapter 418: Challenger (挑戦者)
  • Chapter 419: The Message of Fire (炎のメッセージ)
  • Chapter 420: Lamia Scale's Thank-You Party (蛇姫の鱗感謝祭)
name: Volume 49

description: A bloodbath ensues as the assassins infiltrate a medical clinic to terminate Maggie and the unborn child she is carrying, but will a loose cannon and divine intervention ruin their mission? You don't miss this action packed next chapter of the God Child series. From co-creator D.J. Coffman (Hero By Night).
name: Chapter Two

description: It's chaos in Crawford, Texas when one of Lucy's old inventions kick starts an invasion from an alternate Earth. Solomon and Lucy find themselves on the front line fighting strange invaders. Also in this issue, a special back-up story featuring Sergio Calvet's Skyjack and the Forty Thieves!

The Hungry Game

In post-apocalyptic Canada, guns don't kill people - slapshots do.

For the mutated tribes trying to survive nuclear winter - which is like normal Canadian winter, just more radioactive - hockey serves as a form of ritual warfare in which communities gamble their resources on the abilities of their squad to score goals and bust heads on the ice.

When a starving Red Deer squad rolls into town desperate for a win (and dinner), the Atomics use the opportunity to test out their post-apocalyptic power grid - an enormous potato - as well as their second line. What could possibly go wrong?
name: 1st Period: The Hungry Game

description:
The Shadow Nebula

1933. The Central Hive, a sinister base of operations for an impending invasion of sludge monsters, has been destroyed. It appears as if Earth is saved. Ben Wilcott and Molly Sloan, now in love, can make plans for the future. Timmy Mendez can move on to become a beat reporter in his own right. Jean-Pierre Desperois can go back to what he does best: smuggling salt. Except for one small problem. Now a giant spacecraft hovers above our heroes' heads...
name: The Shadow Nebula

description: Lazerman's disappearance after his battle at the Statue of Liberty has left many wondering if he really exists. But just as he is ready to make his return, the city finds itself under attack by a legion of the zombies! Is Lazerman recovered enough to take on a horde of the undead? And is this really the beginning of a zombie apocalypse, or is there a more sinister hand at work?
name: Night of the Necrolord

description:
Acquiesce 2 of 4

When government agencies come to archaeologist Laila McCarthy for assistance, they are unaware her knowledge of dangerous relics was gained first-hand. But ancient enemies remember her as Sumerian demon Lamashtu and the first vampire.

Laila and William have been captured and need to escape. Or do they?
name: Acquiesce 2 of 4

description: With Walter dead, Jack, Morgan, Jonathan, and Caleb must press on to Macedonia in search of the body of Alexander the Great.

In this issue...

76 Action-Packed Pages in the Mighty Marvel Manner!

Brace yourselves for the final battle between Captain America and Arnim Zola!

Also: Tony Stark faces the robot Death's Head in a trial by combat! Trouble is, the metal menace is 35 feet tall!

Plus: while Thor the present and Thor of the future race across the cosmos to confront Gorr, young Thor suffers as a slave!

By Rick Remender, John Romita Jr, Kieron Gillen, Greg Land, Jason Aaron and Esad Ribic!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Vol.7 #9, Iron Man Vol.6 #7 and Thor: God of Thunder #8!

76 pages of Marvel Universe action!

Daredevil is heading for a new life in San Francisco – but a deadly double and some lethal androids are barring his way! By Mark Waid and Peter Krause!

Apex holds the fate of the young heroes in her hands in the stunning final chapter of 'Avengers Arena'! By Dennis Hopeless and Kev Walker!

Featuring material first published in Daredevil #0.1 and Avengers Arena #18.

Chapter Two: Discovery

Things continue to get explosive for Michael Lane when another one of his former associates is murdered. As the police move to protect him, can Lane keep his hidden past secret for much longer? Only Russell Lissau (THE BATMAN STRIKES!) and John Bivens (DARK ENGINE) know for sure!

Note: The digital edition (5/6/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Discovery

description:
First Meetings

Discover how Alex met Darrel and Serah before things took a turn for the worse in Lighthaven City. Also learn the tale behind Alex's favorite "SK" beanie hat!
name: First Meetings

description:
Curse of the Dreadnuts

Pick up the third issue of the amazing adventures of the Samurnauts! After Master Al made the ultimate sacrifice to save Sora from the clutches of Captain BlackStar, what will happen to the Samurnauts of the future? And in the past, what will become the Reiki, as he's captured aboard the Dreadnut's ship... stranded in space? Only one way to find out... pick up the issue!
name: Curse of the Dreadnuts

description: Broke and directionless, the three members of the metal band Satanic Hell arrive in Texas for a chance tour set up by a mysterious promoter named Sam. Death Priest, Dante, and Exodus quickly find trouble in the bizarre world of Texas, now an authoritarian Christian state controlled by a council of religious fanatics.

This issue contains the following stories:

TIME AGENT Z - That Killer Smile

Z must investigate the appearance of Radioluminescent paint in Leonardo DaVinci's tool box.

RELATIVE SPACE - Journal Entry 002

Icky wakes up on an unknown planet surrounded by strange aliens.

DOGTOWN - For Your Own Good

A single mother struggles to find work in the middle of a city suffering from urban decay.
name: Vol. 4

description:
Chapter 8

Ally goes to her boss for extra work. The job she's given is to break her mother out of prison.
name: Chapter 8

description: The lethal Tangerine comes to Valhalla and he's got just one thing on his mind: kill Dr. Rocket by any means necessary. Plus: Fidel Castro shares women and barbecue with one of the Fogeys. No, we're not kidding.

During a glider flight training course, Yoko makes a landing near an important telecommunication centre, and there meets a mysterious English Lord. A fortuitous encounter that will propel the young woman and her friends into an incredible adventure – her combined skills as a pilot and an electronic engineer make her the ideal candidate for an insane project: land a glider clandestinely inside a crater at the border of China, Russia and Afghanistan.
name: Message For Eternity

description: Cover story is a reprint of The Avengers #60 - ... Till Death Do Us Part
name: 'Til Death Do Us Part

description:
1. A Fine Romance (by Eddie Campbell)

2. Somewhere, a Place (by Ian Wieczorek)

3. These People... (by Phil Elliott)

4. The Beauty of Nature (1 pg. illustration)

name: El Ultimo Arkham: Parte Tres de Cuatro

description: "THE FIELD GUIDE", spotlights the pivotal characters and monstrous creatures appearing in Enormous Season One (#1-6) via in-depth cast profiles, a bestiary, and the making of Enormous-from script to print. Features COLOSSAL: TALES OF ENORMOUS - the new, original, first installment of the companion series illustrated by Jason Copland (POP) and colored by Matthew Battaglia (ROCHE LIMIT). The FIELD GUIDE contains a thorough story summary and revealing insight into the world of ENORMOUS-- an immersive recap designed to fully prepare current and new readers to join the series for Season 2!

name: Man Has Broken the Ties of Earth and is About to Conquer Space

description: A preview of Devil's Due Entertainment's newest title 7 DAYS of DEATH by Jordan Michael Johnson. Get to know Robert Boyd and his humble snowy abode that is constantly disrupted by demons. This little sneak peek gives you a feel for 7 DAYS of DEATH.

As a made man and the underboss of the Lucieso Crime Family, Danny "The Beak" Scicero is a wealthy and powerful man. That is, until the day he was arrested and charged with a slew of crimes. Now, the Lucieso crime family needs to get to Scicero before he can testify and turn states evidence against the family to whom he swore his allegiance.

Gaby is an immigration lawyer in the city of San Diego. One fateful day, an array of seemingly random incidents happen and suddenly she finds herself face-to-face with Anatoly, a member of the Russian mafia. With her instincts screaming at her to stay as far away from him as possible and her heart fluttering at the sight of him, Gaby is confused as to what she should do when Anatoly makes his feelings known to her.
name: Count On A Cop

description: When Agent Paulson finds himself between a rock and a hard place, he betrays his own conscience with terrible results.

As Aero-Girl, Jacqueline Mackenzie is the protector of Foxbay. As the sidekick to Battle Jack, her father, her life couldn’t be any better; but tragedy is just around the corne! Will she be ready to defend her city against the evil of Dr. Chimera and his army of AniMen? Can Aero-Girl be the hero she (and her father) always dreamed of being?

Perceivers

Soldiers finding out a secret that change the course of there live for ever.
name: Perceivers

description:
Angel with a Bullet inspired by Tom Waits's "Romeo is Bleeding".

Gut-shot and betrayed, undercover narco Agent Angelo Carlos has one last chance to make his case.

A great way to introduce Asylum Press to retailers and fans. Featuring a sampling on new and upcoming comics. The Vampire Verses:This debut issue introduces Angelika, an exotic dancer in the NYC club scene who is unwittingly turned into a creature of the night. As she tries to make sense of what she has become she learns of a bloody Vampire War that is being fought in the streets and subway tunnels of New York City.

Black Powder #3, a bloody frontier adventure, by Dwayne Harris, can be described as a "Buckskin Apocalypse Now". Robert Young and his crew set out on the Mississippi River in search of Molly Livingston, who has been captured by the ruthless river pirate Samuel Mason.

Farmhouse is a tale of a drifter who falls in love with an artist undergoing an experimental art therapy regimen, by Elizabeth J. Musgrave and Szymon Kudranski. Also features a retro horror tale by Jason Paulos from his EEEK! series.

Steve Mannion's feisty action hero is back! Can she escape the clutches of "One-Eyed Hans"? Tune in and get the skinny! Meet "One-Eyed Hans", the roughest, toughest, meanest old hombre ever to bust up the FEARLESS DAWN camp!

OEUVRE

Expecting to sample the delights of contemporary sculpture's boldest and brightest, the international art glitterati descend upon London's V&A museum.

However, when the centrepiece of the exhibition turns out to be the corpse of a missing artist, the private view becomes a hunt for a killer with the hands of a craftsman.

Introducing Gabriel Blake, the 'Blind Detective.'
name: Oeuvre

description: Bodie thinks he's a big, scary troll, yet everyone in the village of Hagadorn knows he's cute and cuddly. But that won't stop a monster hunter from making a trophy out of Bodie!

Dark Horse Comics is proud to present a series of digital sampler comics, Builds Characters. Each sampler will focus on a single creator and excerpt variety of their past and upcoming works with Dark Horse.

Enjoy this free sampling from Eisner Award–winning writer and artist Cameron Stewart, featuring a choice selection of the hotly anticipated Fight Club 2, as well as excerpts from B.P.R.D., Tales of the Vampire, and Sin Titulo!

Ed Brubaker's award-winning Captain America run concludes! As Captain America's staunch ally Bucky, James Buchanan Barnes was one of America's greatest heroes of WWII - until he was brainwashed into becoming the Soviet spy known as the Winter Soldier. Now, in the aftermath of FEAR ITSELF, James is the Winter Soldier again! When Russian sleeper agents awaken and old enemies resurface with new identities, Winter Soldier and Black Widow clash with Dr. Doom - and James must save the Widow from her own past! But even with help from Wolverine and Hawkeye, must Bucky sacrifice everything to save his love? Meanwhile, Captain America takes on Scourge and the Discordians, while a deadly villain from the past reveals a mystery spanning generations of heroes! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA AND BUCKY #620-628, FEAR ITSELF #7.1: CAPTAIN AMERICA, WINTER SOLDIER #1-14 and CAPTAIN AMERICA (2011) #11-19.
name: HC

volume.name: Captain America: Return of the Winter Soldier Omnibus

description: Polly replies to an advertisement to become a surrogate mother in order to cover the costs of her mother's surgery. But her world is rocked when her mother dies soon after Polly becomes pregnant. Devastated and alone, Polly goes to live in a house prepared for her by the biological father. Soon after, she discovers that the biological father, a rich bachelor, chose to go with a surrogate because of his deep lack of trust in women. So why does he continue to try to get close to her, keeping his true identity a secret?
name: The Husband Hunters III

description: From the pages of the Mis-Adventures of Adam West comes this new action packed space adventure. Dirk Benedict-- "Starbuck" in the original Battlestar Galactica and The A-Team's "Faceman"-- is signing autographs at a convention when a mysterious scientist appears, transporting Dirk to Earth's far-flung future, where he discovers he's mankind's only hope against an oppressive computer and its robot army!
name: TPB

description:
Myth Conceptions

Dominos, a group of superheroes employed by the United States government to fight for the safety of the entire planet. But when a critical mission goes off the rails and out of control, the team is forced to make decisions that will change everything. And there won't be any going back.
name: Myth Conceptions
